g.title: leaf_28
g.text: First we need to actually nail down lines and offsets in the various classes.

g.title: leaf_30
g.text: That's going to be some exacting and chasey code. Good behavior now will pay off

g.title: leaf_32
g.text: Once the classes all behave as promised, pushing out an in-memory source map
is relatively straightforward. We traverse a doc building a string, so we
have the information readily at hand and just need to pass it along.

g.title: leaf_34
g.text: Turning it into crazypants encoded offset format is the step after that.

g.title: leaf_36
g.text: We can make good use of the not wacky version.
